So you are going by a proxy?  Sounds like you&#39;ve successfully told maven 
how to download jars over the proxy but the resolver used fetching 
stylesheets/DTDs needs also to be told to go via the proxy.   After a 
quick survey, I&#39;m unable to find direct java system properties or 
config. for javax.xml.transform package to have it go via a proxy.   
Looking at the sdocbook plugin page -- 
http://maven-plugins.sourceforge.net/maven-sdocbook-plugin/properties.html 
-- it looks like you can stop the resolver going to the net altogether 
and have it use copies on local disk, but would take a little work.
St.Ack

